                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 13.729,
                                "byte_start": 73658,
                                "byte_stop": 128620,
                                "text": "The judgments and opinion of the Court in 75-62, Runyon against McCrary and three related cases will be announced by Mr. Justice Stewart."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 13.729,
                        "stop": 846.721,
                        "byte_start": 128620,
                        "byte_stop": 3460590,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15043,
                            "name": "Potter Stewart",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/potter_stewart",
                            "last_name": "Stewart",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2687,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": -353962800,
                                    "date_end": 362984400,
                                    "appointing_president": "Dwight D. Eisenhower",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2687"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32752,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 56350,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/potter_stewart.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 8298,
                            "identifier": "potter_stewart"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 13.729,
                                "stop": 23.158,
                                "byte_start": 128620,
                                "byte_stop": 166340,
                                "text": "These cases are here by the reason of the grant of writs of certiorari to the United States Court of Appeals for the Fourth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 23.158,
                                "stop": 46.288,
                                "byte_start": 166340,
                                "byte_stop": 258814,
                                "text": "The principal issue presented by these consolidated cases is whether a federal law, namely Section 1981 of Volume 42 of the United States Code, prohibits commercially operated private schools from excluding qualified children solely because they are Negroes."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 46.288,
                                "stop": 50.713,
                                "byte_start": 258814,
                                "byte_stop": 276577,
                                "text": "That law in pertinent part reads as follows."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 50.713,
                                "stop": 65.816,
                                "byte_start": 276577,
                                "byte_stop": 336972,
                                "text": "\u201cAll persons within the jurisdiction of the United States shall have the same right in every State and Territory to make and enforce contracts\u00a0as is enjoyed by white citizens.\u201d"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 65.816,
                                "stop": 74.599,
                                "byte_start": 336972,
                                "byte_stop": 372081,
                                "text": "The respondents in number 75-62, Michael McCrary and Colin Gonzales are Negro children."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 74.599,
                                "stop": 79.585,
                                "byte_start": 372081,
                                "byte_stop": 392038,
                                "text": "By their parents, they filed a class action against the petitioners in that case."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 79.585,
                                "stop": 86.81,
                                "byte_start": 392038,
                                "byte_stop": 420982,
                                "text": "Russell and Katheryne Runyon, who are the proprietors of Bobbe\u0027s private School in Arlington, Virginia."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 86.81,
                                "stop": 98.796,
                                "byte_start": 420982,
                                "byte_stop": 468943,
                                "text": "Their complaint alleged that they had been prevented from attending the school because of the petitioners\u0027 policy of denying admission to Negroes, in violation of Section 1981."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 98.796,
                                "stop": 120.731,
                                "byte_start": 468943,
                                "byte_stop": 556610,
                                "text": "They sought declaratory and injunctive relief and monetary damages. On the same day, Colin Gonzales, the respondent in No. 75-66, filed a similar complaint by his parents against the petitioner in that case, Fairfax-Brewster School located in Fairfax County, Virginia."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 120.731,
                                "stop": 133.305,
                                "byte_start": 556610,
                                "byte_stop": 606974,
                                "text": "The petitioner in No. 75-278, the Southern Independent School Association, sought and was granted permission to intervene as a party defendant in the suit against the Runyons."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 133.305,
                                "stop": 146.307,
                                "byte_start": 606974,
                                "byte_stop": 658905,
                                "text": "That organization is a nonprofit association, composed of six state private school associations, and represents 395 private schools."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 146.307,
                                "stop": 151.924,
                                "byte_start": 658905,
                                "byte_stop": 681371,
                                "text": "It is stipulated that many of these schools deny admission to Negroes."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 151.924,
                                "stop": 155.03,
                                "byte_start": 681371,
                                "byte_stop": 693805,
                                "text": "The suits were consolidated for trial."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 155.03,
                                "stop": 162.151,
                                "byte_start": 693805,
                                "byte_stop": 722331,
                                "text": "The findings of the District Court, which were left undisturbed by the Court of Appeals, were as follows."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 162.151,
                                "stop": 172.737,
                                "byte_start": 722331,
                                "byte_stop": 764649,
                                "text": "Bobbe\u0027s School opened in 1958 and grew from an initial enrollment of five students to 200 students in 1972."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 172.737,
                                "stop": 179.251,
                                "byte_start": 764649,
                                "byte_stop": 790667,
                                "text": "A day camp was begun in 1967 and has averaged 100 children per year."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 179.251,
                                "stop": 200.835,
                                "byte_start": 790667,
                                "byte_stop": 877080,
                                "text": "The Fairfax-Brewster School commenced operations in 1955 and opened a summer day camp in 1956. A total of 223 students were enrolled at the school during the 1972-1973 academic year, and 236 attended the day camp in the summer of 1972."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 200.835,
                                "stop": 207.15,
                                "byte_start": 877080,
                                "byte_stop": 902262,
                                "text": "Neither school has ever accepted a Negro child for any of its programs."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 207.15,
                                "stop": 222.811,
                                "byte_start": 902262,
                                "byte_stop": 964956,
                                "text": "In response to a mailed brochure addressed \u0022resident\u0022 and an advertisement in the \u0022Yellow Pages\u0022 of the telephone directory, Mr. and Mrs. Gonzales telephoned and then visited the Fairfax-Brewster School in May of 1969."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 222.811,
                                "stop": 229.329,
                                "byte_start": 964956,
                                "byte_stop": 991078,
                                "text": "After the visit, they submitted an application for their son Colin\u0027s admission to the day camp."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 229.329,
                                "stop": 236.734,
                                "byte_start": 991078,
                                "byte_stop": 1020649,
                                "text": "The school responded with a formal letter, which stated that the school was \u0022unable to accommodate Colin\u0027s application.\u0022"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 236.734,
                                "stop": 239.38,
                                "byte_start": 1020649,
                                "byte_stop": 1031202,
                                "text": "Mr. Gonzales telephoned the school."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 239.38,
                                "stop": 246.595,
                                "byte_start": 1031202,
                                "byte_stop": 1060042,
                                "text": "Fairfax-Brewster\u0027s Chairman of the Board explained that the reason for Colin\u0027s rejection was that the school was not integrated."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 246.595,
                                "stop": 255.992,
                                "byte_start": 1060042,
                                "byte_stop": 1097658,
                                "text": "Mr. Gonzales then telephoned Bobbe\u0027s School, from which the family had also received in the mail a brochure addressed simply to \u201cresident.\u201d"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 255.992,
                                "stop": 265.585,
                                "byte_start": 1097658,
                                "byte_stop": 1136006,
                                "text": "In response to a question concerning that school\u0027s admissions policies, he was told that only members of the Caucasian race were accepted."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 265.585,
                                "stop": 273.209,
                                "byte_start": 1136006,
                                "byte_stop": 1166517,
                                "text": "In August of 1972, Mrs. McCrary telephoned Bobbe\u0027s School in response to an advertisement in the telephone book."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 273.209,
                                "stop": 277.176,
                                "byte_start": 1166517,
                                "byte_stop": 1182399,
                                "text": "She inquired about nursery school facilities for her son, Michael."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 277.176,
                                "stop": 280.27,
                                "byte_start": 1182399,
                                "byte_stop": 1194834,
                                "text": "She also asked if the school was integrated."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 280.27,
                                "stop": 283.449,
                                "byte_start": 1194834,
                                "byte_stop": 1207477,
                                "text": "The answer was no."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 283.449,
                                "stop": 298.144,
                                "byte_start": 1207477,
                                "byte_stop": 1266305,
                                "text": "Upon these facts, the District Court found that the Fairfax-Brewster School had rejected Colin Gonzales\u0027 application on account of his race and that Bobbe\u0027s School had denied both children admission on racial grounds."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 298.144,
                                "stop": 306.784,
                                "byte_start": 1266305,
                                "byte_stop": 1300891,
                                "text": "The court held that Section 1981 makes illegal, the schools\u0027 racially discriminatory admissions policies."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 306.784,
                                "stop": 320.169,
                                "byte_start": 1300891,
                                "byte_stop": 1354389,
                                "text": "It therefore enjoined Fairfax-Brewster School and Bobbe\u0027s School and the member schools of the Southern Independent School Association from discriminating against applicants for admission on the basis of race."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 320.169,
                                "stop": 340.653,
                                "byte_start": 1354389,
                                "byte_stop": 1436309,
                                "text": "The court awarded compensatory relief to Mr. and Mrs. McCrary, Michael McCrary, and Colin Gonzales, but the court held that the damages claim of Mr. and Mrs. Gonzales was barred by Virginia\u0027s two-year statute of limitations for personal injury actions, \u0022borrowed\u0022 for Section 1981 suits filed in that State."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 340.653,
                                "stop": 348.283,
                                "byte_start": 1436309,
                                "byte_stop": 1466820,
                                "text": "Finally, the court assessed attorneys\u0027 fees for $1,000 against each of the two schools."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 348.283,
                                "stop": 364.551,
                                "byte_start": 1466820,
                                "byte_stop": 1531918,
                                "text": "The Court of Appeals for the Fourth Circuit, sitting en banc, affirmed the District Court\u0027s grant of equitable and compensatory relief and its ruling as to the applicable statute of limitations, but reversed its award of attorneys\u0027 fees."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 364.551,
                                "stop": 390.33,
                                "byte_start": 1531918,
                                "byte_stop": 1635049,
                                "text": "We granted the petitions for certiorari filed by the Fairfax-Brewster School and that\u0027s case number 75-66; Bobbe\u0027s School in number 75-62; and the Southern Independent School Association number 75-278, to consider whether Section 1981 prevents private schools of this kind from discriminating racially among applicants."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 390.33,
                                "stop": 405.469,
                                "byte_start": 1635049,
                                "byte_stop": 1695549,
                                "text": "We also granted the cross-petition of Michael McCrary, Colin Gonzales, and their parents, in number 75-306 to determine the attorneys\u0027 fees and statute of limitations issues."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 405.469,
                                "stop": 412.023,
                                "byte_start": 1695549,
                                "byte_stop": 1721776,
                                "text": "It is perhaps worth noting that some of the questions that these cases do not present."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 412.023,
                                "stop": 422.572,
                                "byte_start": 1721776,
                                "byte_stop": 1763989,
                                "text": "They do not present any question of the right of a private social organization to limit its membership on racial grounds or any other grounds."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 422.572,
                                "stop": 436.147,
                                "byte_start": 1763989,
                                "byte_stop": 1818324,
                                "text": "They do not present any question of the right of a private school to limit its student body to boys, to girls, or to adherence of a particular religious faith."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 436.147,
                                "stop": 447.842,
                                "byte_start": 1818324,
                                "byte_stop": 1865031,
                                "text": "They do not even present the application of Section 1981 to private sectarian schools that practice racial exclusion on religious grounds."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 447.842,
                                "stop": 451.914,
                                "byte_start": 1865031,
                                "byte_stop": 1881331,
                                "text": "Rather, these cases present only two basic questions."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 451.914,
                                "stop": 472.653,
                                "byte_start": 1881331,
                                "byte_stop": 1964296,
                                "text": "Whether Section 1981 prohibits private, commercially operated, nonsectarian schools from denying admission to prospective students solely because they are Negroes, and, if so, whether that federal law is constitutional as so applied."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 472.653,
                                "stop": 507.584,
                                "byte_start": 1964296,
                                "byte_stop": 2103999,
                                "text": "It is now well established that Section 1981 enacted under the power conferred upon Congress by Section 2 of the Thirteenth Amendment, prohibits racial discrimination in the making and enforcement of private contracts and we think it is apparent that the racial exclusion practiced by the Fairfax-Brewster School and Bobbe\u0027s Private School amounts to a classic violation of Section 1981."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 507.584,
                                "stop": 518.109,
                                "byte_start": 2103999,
                                "byte_stop": 2146109,
                                "text": "The parents of Colin Gonzales and Michael McCrary sought to enter into contractual relationships with Bobbe\u0027s School for educational services."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 518.109,
                                "stop": 525.114,
                                "byte_start": 2146109,
                                "byte_stop": 2174216,
                                "text": "Colin Gonzales\u0027 parents sought to enter into a similar relationship with the Fairfax-Brewster School."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 525.114,
                                "stop": 536.972,
                                "byte_start": 2174216,
                                "byte_stop": 2221550,
                                "text": "Under these contractual relationships, the schools would have received payments for services rendered, and the prospective students would have received instruction in return for those payments."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 536.972,
                                "stop": 553,
                                "byte_start": 2221550,
                                "byte_stop": 2285707,
                                "text": "The educational services of Bobbe\u0027s Private School and the Fairfax-Brewster School were advertised and offered to members of the general public,but neither school offered services on an equal basis to white and nonwhite students."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 553,
                                "stop": 568.146,
                                "byte_start": 2285707,
                                "byte_stop": 2346311,
                                "text": "As the Court of Appeals held, \u0022there is ample evidence in the record to support the trial judge\u0027s factual determinations that Colin Gonzales and Michael McCrary were denied admission to the schools because of their race."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 568.146,
                                "stop": 583.922,
                                "byte_start": 2346311,
                                "byte_stop": 2409423,
                                "text": "\u0022The Court of Appeals\u0027 conclusion that Section 1981 was thereby violated follows, we think inexorably, from the language of that statute, as construed in our previous cases."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 583.922,
                                "stop": 599.909,
                                "byte_start": 2409423,
                                "byte_stop": 2473371,
                                "text": "The question remains whether Section 1981 as applied, violates constitutionally protected rights of free association and privacy, or a parent\u0027s right to direct the education of his children."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 599.909,
                                "stop": 609.535,
                                "byte_start": 2473371,
                                "byte_stop": 2511823,
                                "text": "In a series of decisions, the Court has recognized a First Amendment right to engage in association for the advancement of beliefs and ideas."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 609.535,
                                "stop": 626.81,
                                "byte_start": 2511823,
                                "byte_stop": 2580995,
                                "text": "From this principle it may be assumed that parents have a First Amendment right to send their children to educational institutions that promote the belief that racial segregation is desirable, and that the children have an equal right to attend such institutions."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 626.81,
                                "stop": 651.124,
                                "byte_start": 2580995,
                                "byte_stop": 2678171,
                                "text": "But it does not follow that the practice of excluding racial minorities from such institutions is also protected by the same principle and as the Court of Appeals noted, \u0022there is no showing that discontinuance of the discriminatory admission practices would inhibit in any way the teaching in these schools of any ideas or dogma."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 651.124,
                                "stop": 684.113,
                                "byte_start": 2678171,
                                "byte_stop": 2810141,
                                "text": "\u0022In Meyer against Nebraska, good many years ago, the Court held that the liberty protected by the Due Process Clause of the Fourteenth Amendment, includes the right to send one\u0027s children to a private school that offers specialized training, in that case, instruction in the German language and that doctrine was expanded in the later case of Pierce against Society of Sisters and much more recent case of Wisconsin against Yoder."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 684.113,
                                "stop": 694.548,
                                "byte_start": 2810141,
                                "byte_stop": 2851937,
                                "text": "It is clear that the present application of Section 1981 infringes no such constitutional right as was recognized in those cases."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 694.548,
                                "stop": 710.83,
                                "byte_start": 2851937,
                                "byte_stop": 2917034,
                                "text": "No challenge is made to the petitioner\u0027s right to operate their private schools or the right of parents to send their children to a particular private school rather than to a public school nor do these cases involve a challenge to the subject matter which is taught at any private school."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 710.83,
                                "stop": 725.04,
                                "byte_start": 2917034,
                                "byte_stop": 2973877,
                                "text": "Thus, the Fairfax-Brewster School and Bobbe\u0027s Private School and members of the intervenor association remain free to inculcate whatever values and standards they think desirable."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 725.04,
                                "stop": 731.468,
                                "byte_start": 2973877,
                                "byte_stop": 2999581,
                                "text": "The Court has held that in some situations the Constitution confers a right of privacy."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 731.468,
                                "stop": 747.4,
                                "byte_start": 2999581,
                                "byte_stop": 3063320,
                                "text": "While the application of Section 1981to the conduct at issue here does not represent governmental intrusion into the privacy of the home or a similarly intimate setting, it does implicate parental interests."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 747.4,
                                "stop": 759.283,
                                "byte_start": 3063320,
                                "byte_stop": 3110863,
                                "text": "These interests are related to in a cogent kind of way to the to the pro-creative rights protected in such cases as Roe against Wade and Griswold against Connecticut."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 759.283,
                                "stop": 772.078,
                                "byte_start": 3110863,
                                "byte_stop": 3162063,
                                "text": "But the court has repeatedly stressed that while parents do have a constitutional right to send their children to private schools and a constitutional right to select private schools that offer specialized instruction."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 772.078,
                                "stop": 782.039,
                                "byte_start": 3162063,
                                "byte_stop": 3201874,
                                "text": "They have no constitutional right to provide their children with private school education unfettered by reasonable government regulation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 782.039,
                                "stop": 803.11,
                                "byte_start": 3201874,
                                "byte_stop": 3286197,
                                "text": "For these and other reasons, spelled out in some detail in the court\u0027s written opinion, we agree with the Court of Appeals that enforcement of Section 1981 in these cases will not work a deprivation of any constitutional right of the defendant schools, of the intervenors or of their pupils or patrons."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 803.11,
                                "stop": 818.723,
                                "byte_start": 3286197,
                                "byte_stop": 3348577,
                                "text": "For the reasons stated in the Court\u0027s written opinion, we also agree with the Court of Appeals disposition of the subsidiary issues involving the statute of limitations and the award of attorney fees."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 818.723,
                                "stop": 833.541,
                                "byte_start": 3348577,
                                "byte_stop": 3407823,
                                "text": "For the reasons I have summarized which are elaborated at considerable length in the Court\u0027s written opinion filed with the clerk today, the judgment of the Court of Appeals is in all respects affirmed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 833.541,
                                "stop": 840.606,
                                "byte_start": 3407823,
                                "byte_stop": 3436140,
                                "text": "Mr. Justice Powell and Mr. Justice Stevens while joining the court\u0027s opinion have each filed concurring opinions."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 840.606,
                                "stop": 846.721,
                                "byte_start": 3436140,
                                "byte_stop": 3460590,
                                "text": "Mr. Justice White has filed a dissenting opinion in which he has been joined by Mr. Justice Rehnquist."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 846.721,
                        "stop": 848.473,
